Selecting the right makeup artist goes beyond social media aesthetics, it requires clear communication and informed decision-making. 

Before confirming your booking, consider asking the following key questions:

What services are included in the package (trial, touch-ups, travel, etc.)?

Are you available on my event date and time?

Could you share a portfolio of similar looks or client transformations?

Which makeup brands and products do you typically use, and are they suitable for sensitive or specific skin types?

How do you cater to different skin tones and textures?

Do you offer a trial session prior to the event?

What is your cancellation and rescheduling policy?

How much time do you require for the complete makeup process?

Will you be working alone or with an assistant if there are multiple clients?

What hygiene and sanitization practices do you follow?

These questions help ensure that your experience is seamless, professional, and aligned with your expectations. 

A clear communication today leads to a confident and flawless look on the day that matters most.

For inquiries or trial appointments, please reach out via direct message.

Selecting the right bridal makeup look is an important decision that sets the tone for your overall appearance on the big day. 

If you’re caught between opting for a full glam or soft glam look, here’s a breakdown to guide your choice:

✨ Full Glam: Best suited for brides who want a bold, statement look. This style features defined eyes, contoured features, dramatic lashes, and a flawless finish—ideal for evening weddings and grand celebrations where you want to make a lasting impression.

🌸 Soft Glam: A timeless choice for brides who prefer elegance with subtlety. With a focus on natural tones, dewy skin, and softly blended eyeshadows, this look enhances your features without overpowering them—perfect for daytime functions or intimate settings.

Both looks can be tailored to match your personality, outfit, and event type. 

A bridal trial can help you visualize and finalize the look that makes you feel your absolute best.

Book your consultation today and let’s create a bridal look that truly reflects you.

Choosing the perfect bridal hairstyle can feel overwhelming — but it doesn’t have to be! 

The key is to match your hairstyle with your face shape, outfit neckline, hair texture, and overall bridal vibe.

Round face? Opt for volume on top or a sleek middle part to elongate your face.

Heart-shaped face? Soft curls or a side bun adds balance.

Wearing a heavy dupatta or veil? Go for a secure low bun or braid to hold it in place all day.

Off-shoulder or sweetheart neckline? Consider loose curls, half-up styles, or side-swept waves to enhance the neckline.

During your bridal trial, I’ll guide you through options that not only complement your features but also stay intact throughout your big day. 💍✨

💌 Book your bridal consultation now and let’s find your perfect look!

As a makeup artist, my goal isn’t just to create a flawless look—it’s to offer an experience filled with trust, comfort, and care. 

There are certain things I never charge for, simply because they are part of the love and passion I put into every session:

✨ Skin prep – because great makeup starts with healthy skin.

✨ Last-minute fixes – I’ll always be there to adjust that lash or blend that line.

✨ Friendly advice – from product suggestions to skincare tips, I’m happy to help.

✨ Emotional support – whether you’re a bride or just nervous before an event, I’m your hype person!

✨ Small touch-ups – a quick lipstick fix or extra setting spray is always on me.

✨ Smiles and good vibes – included in every appointment, always! 😊

Because it’s not just about the makeup, it’s about making you feel your absolute best—inside and out. 💕

Planning your dream wedding? Amidst all the excitement, dresses, and decor decisions, don’t forget you are the heart of it all! 

Here are a few things every bride-to-be should keep in mind:

💫 Prioritize self-care – Healthy skin, restful sleep & emotional balance make a huge difference.

💫 Do trials – Makeup, hair, and outfits should be tested well in advance to avoid last-minute stress.

💫 Stay hydrated & eat well – You need energy to shine from within.

💫 Schedule breaks – It’s okay to pause and soak it all in.

💫 Keep a bridal emergency kit – Safety pins, mints, tissues, band-aids—you’ll thank us later!

💫 Choose comfort + style – Make sure your outfit & footwear let you enjoy every moment.

💫 Communicate with your MUA & planner – Clear conversations help bring your vision to life.

💫 Don’t chase perfection – Embrace the real, raw, and beautiful moments.

💫 Enjoy the process – From pre-wedding jitters to sangeet rehearsals, cherish every step.

💫 Remember: you’re the bride, not a checklist – This is YOUR moment, own it with grace.

Take a deep breath, smile, and walk into this new chapter with confidence, beauty, and love 💖
